arch:property.oc:show_val: Later Byzantine reuse of the "paved room."

Munsell 5 YR 4/4 (Reddish Brown). An exceedingly important soil Locus, this material represents a deposit related to late activity in the paved room east of the cryptoporticus junction. A whole Byzantine lamp found in the layer suggests a date; coin finds might corroborate and refine this dating.
Phase X: Site abandonment post major collapse dating to the Byzantine period from the CE 4th through 5th c.
